## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of current data and the potential bias in sources. The ethical and legal landscape of euthanasia is continually evolving, and perspectives may vary significantly across different cultures and legal systems. Additionally, the emotional and subjective nature of the topic can influence both public opinion and scholarly discourse. Further research is needed to explore the long-term effects of euthanasia legalization in countries where it is already permitted.